Haha, the funniest story! During finals week, Michelle, Nic, and I went to the Daly (pronounced Daily, spelt Daly)Scoop for lunch. We are kind of 'usuals' there. I guess that's what happens when you live in a small town--there are only so few places you can eat that aren't exactly fast food. The waitress knows our meal--water and the kid's meal of chicken fingers with a side of BBQ and then our Italian Sodas right before we leave-mine is always Raspberry Vanilla and hers is always Vanilla with cream. Anyways, the day we were in there during finals week, I thought it would be funny to unscrew the tops to the salt and pepper shakers. Well, yesterday, Michelle and I went in to the Daly Scoop for our usual, and the waitress came over and said "Girls, I would appreciate it if you would leave my salt and pepper shakers alone this time." All we could do is act stupid while crack up inside. She totally bought it. She said "oh, maybe it was the guy with you." It was so funny. Totally the highlight of my day....well, until that night! We had such an awesome game against Carson! Very nerve-racking! During the celebration, I got paint all over me from hugging people and the players who had paint rubbed off on them...let me tell you, I did not want to rub one of the paint marks off (only Michelle knows why). Oh well, maybe soon enough. Probably not! Oh well. Only 4 and a half more weeks until NSYNC! Can't wait!
http://soccergurl22.livejournal.com/580.html

Welcome,
Well, this is my first entry of my livejournal! My name is Kim, but the special people in my life call me Kimmie! I am a sophomore at Douglas High School which is in Douglas County, Nevada. Think Carson City. Anyways, I play soccer for Douglas soccer and this past season, our team went 10-0 and took second place in the Zone championships! Besides school sports events and movies and maybe bowling, there isn't really anything to do here. The population of our town is less then 10,000 people, so that might explain it. There is much more to come, but it's past my bedtime and mommy is hounding me to get off!
